The innovation policy course is a good example to introduce the students policy making in a field under vivid discussions concerning the reasons, mechanism and policies related to the innovativeness of the economy. Often the mechanisms that the governments can choose are controversial, and therefore on the course, the roles of public and private, but also third sectors are discussed, but also the appropriate policies to impact these roles. Although the main focus is on different innovation policy aspects, during the course the overview is provided of the literature trying to explain the emergence of innovations, and the reasons why some firms, sectors or economies perform better. Here the crucial role of policies is presented throughout the course on the basis of examples on the level of enterprise, sector, region, country and EU.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course aims to deepen the innovation and technology management students' knowledge about different innovation policy aspects that of improve the innovative performance of firms.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student successfully passing the course is able: 1. To analyse the innovation capabilities and sectoral innovation specifics of different firms (organisations) and to offer solutions for developing innovative capabilities of specific firm (organisation) or industry; 3. To analyse the innovation systems and policies and propse solutions for improving innovation policy in a specific field.
